        <title type="html"><![CDATA[I Got Murdered]]></title>
        <id>/2022/03/31/i-got-murdered</id>
        <link href="https://robertjcolley.com/chess-blog/2022/03/31/i-got-murdered"/>
        <updated>2022-03-31T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[Brutal loss I suffered, and what I learned from it]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>This was a tough game. I got murdered by my opponent. This is called the <a href="https://chesspathways.com/chess-openings/kings-pawn-opening/wayward-queen-attack/">Wayward Queen Attack</a>, and to defend it I had to play Nc6 then g6. This forces the queen back, and then if the queen goes back to e3, I play Nf6.</p><p><img src="/img/chess/2022-03-31-i-got-murdered/board.gif" alt="solid game"/></p>]]></content>
